    <refnamediv>
        <refname>glIsSync</refname>
        <refpurpose>determine if a name corresponds to a sync object</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <funcsynopsis>
            <funcprototype>
                <funcdef>GLboolean <function>glIsSync</function></funcdef>
                <paramdef>GLsync <parameter>sync</parameter></paramdef>
            </funcprototype>
        </funcsynopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection xml:id="parameters"><info><title>Parameters</title></info>
        <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
            <term><parameter>sync</parameter></term>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Specifies a value that may be the name of a sync object.
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection xml:id="description"><info><title>Description</title></info>
        <para>
            <function>glIsSync</function> returns <constant>GL_TRUE</constant> if <parameter>sync</parameter> is currently the name of a sync object.
            If <parameter>sync</parameter> is not the name of a sync object, or if an error occurs, <function>glIsSync</function> returns
            <constant>GL_FALSE</constant>. Note that zero is not the name of a sync object.
        </para>
    </refsection>
    <refsection xml:id="notes"><info><title>Notes</title></info>
        <para>
            <function>glIsSync</function> is available only if the GL version is 3.2 or greater.
        </para>
    </refsection>
